{
  "doc_id": "44000",
  "text": "• Nearest Neighbor: The nearest neighbor (NN) is considered as one of the most common initial population seeding technique. NN may still good alternative to random initial population technique in order to generate an initial population solutions that are used in solving TSP with GAs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In the case of NN technique, the generation of each individual starts by selecting random city as the starting city and then the nearest city to be added as the new starting city. Iteratively, NN adds the nearest city to the current city that was not added to the individual until the individual includes all the cities in the problem space. The generated individuals from the NN population seeding can improve the evolving search process in the next generations as they were created from a city nearest to the current city [CITATION_6] .",
